member.summary:
            The minimum value is the lower bound of the range.

Condition: The class must return a static value. Two instances of the same class can't have different ranges.
            Example: public T Minimum => 0;

            The maximum value is the upper bound of the range.

Condition: The class must return a static value. Two instances of the same class can't have different ranges.
            Example: public T Maximum => 100;

            True if the range includes the minimum value (the lower bound) itself.

Condition: The class must return a static value. Two instances of the same class can't have different ranges.
            Example: public bool RangeIncludesTheMinimum => true;

            True if the range includes the maximum value (the upper bound) itself.

Condition: The class must return a static value. Two instances of the same class can't have different ranges.
            Example: public bool RangeIncludesTheMaximum => true;

            To String transcoding functions.

You have to include three additional static functions:
            public static  ParseFromInvariantString(string s)
            and
            public static  ParseFromString(string s)
            and
            public static  ParseFromString(string s, IFormatProvider provider)

Gets the  of an instance field.


Example: var fieldName = MemberInfoOf.InstanceField<TestClass, int>(a => a.Field1).Name;
Example: var fieldType = MemberInfoOf.InstanceField<TestClass, int>(a => a.Field1).FieldType;

Gets the  of an instance property.


Example: var propertyName = MemberInfoOf.InstanceProperty<TestClass, int>(a => a.Property1).Name;
Example: var propertyType = MemberInfoOf.InstanceProperty<TestClass, int>(a => a.Property1).PropertyType;

Gets the  of an instance member (field or property).
Note: you do not need an actual instance.
Example with an instance class field: var instanceFieldName = MemberInfoOf.InstanceFieldOrProperty<Program, int>(u => u.instanceField).Name;

Gets the  of an instance or static function.
Note: for an instance function on a class type, you need an actual instance (null is not valid).
Example: var thisInstanceFunctionName = MemberInfoOf.Function((Action)this.InstanceFunction).Name;
Example: var staticFunctionName = MemberInfoOf.Function((Func<MemberInfo, int>)test.staticFunction).Name;

Gets the  of an instance (not static) function.
Note: you do not need an actual instance.
Example: var instanceFunctionName = MemberInfoOf.InstanceFunction<Program>(u => (Func<MemberInfo, int>)u.InstanceFunction);

Gets the name of an instance member (field or property).
Note: you do not need an actual instance.
Example with an instance class field: var instanceFieldName = NameOf<Program, int>(u => u.instanceField);

Gets the name of an instance or static function.
Note: for an instance function on a class type, you need an actual instance (null is not valid).
Example: var thisInstanceFunctionName = NameOf.Function((Action)this.InstanceFunction);
Example: var staticFunctionName = NameOf.Function((Func<string, int>)test.staticFunction);

Gets the name of an instance (not static) function.
Note: you do not need an actual instance.
Example: var instanceFunctionName = NameOf.InstanceFunction<Program>(u => (Func<string, int>)u.InstanceFunction);
